</div><!--end sidebar--><div id="main"><div class="entry"><h2 class="socialshareheading">The Need For A Supply Of Safe Drinking Water</h2>
<p>Water&#8230; We can&#8217;t live without it. Pure, clean water is an absolute must for our survival. Experts estimate that over 1 billion people lack safe drinking water. That&#8217;s nearly a quarter of the world&#8217;s population. Each year, more than five million people die from water-related diseases; four million of them are children. You might be faced with a critical situation where lives hang in the balance…. Or…. Maybe finding safe water is just simply impractical or inconvenient. Whether you&#8217;re providing aid to regions affected by the ravages of Mother Nature, assisting third-world nations with insufficient infrastructures or simply confronted with remote terrain that lacks effective water treatment methods, an abundant, safe and healthy drinking water supply is always the highest priority. Noah Water Systems was formed by individuals who have been involved in disaster relief and humanitarian efforts worldwide for over 30 years.</p>
<h2>As Often Is The Case, Necessity Is The Mother Of Invention</h2>
<p>This group of disaster relief volunteers analyzed the problem and developed a solution in a portable, self-contained, comprehensive water purification system. The Trekker “version 1.0” was created and Noah Water Systems was formed with the intent of producing and distributing their water purification products worldwide.</p>
<h2>Field Tested, Effectiveness Proven</h2>
<p>The experts at Noah have tested, refined, and retested their portable water purification units in extremes ranging from the Panamanian jungles to Sub-Saharan Africa to the frozen lakes and ponds in Michigan winter. The results demonstrate that Noah’s products, which combine sediment and carbon filtration along with patented ultraviolet technology, provide clean, safe and healthy drinking water. <a href="http://www.noahwatersystems.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/NoahWaterParagonLabsTestResults.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Independent laboratory testing</a> confirmed the treated water to be greater than 99.99% free of the bacteria and virus introduced. All of the Noah products effectively treat the following waterborne bacteria, virus and conditions:</p>
<div class="contenthomecontainer">
<div class="column1of2">
<ul>
<li>Giardia</li>
<li>Gastroenteritis</li>
<li>Cryptosporidium</li>
<li>Enteric Fever</li>
<li>Diptheria</li>
<li>Typhoid Fever</li>
<li>E. Coli</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="column2of2">
<ul>
<li>Cholera</li>
<li>Legionnaires Disease</li>
<li>Dysentery</li>
<li>Infectious Jaundice</li>
<li>Staphylococcus Infections</li>
<li>Tuberculosis Causative</li>
<li>Streptococcus Infections</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<p>Additionally, sediment, organic matter, volatile chemicals, THM’s, pesticides and herbicides are effectively reduced to provide clean, clear and SAFE drinking water.</p>
<h2>Two Models Introduced</h2>
<p>The result is the introduction of two totally self-contained water purification systems: the <a href="http://www.noahwater.com/products/trekker/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">1-gpm Trekker</a> and the <a href="http://www.noahwater.com/products/nomad/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">25-gpm Nomad</a>. While differing in size, flow-rate and cost, both have been designed with ease of use in mind.</p>
<br /><div class="clear"></div></div><div id="commentsection">
